  "body": "We've got some use cases where we need to proxy requests to S3 buckets which require authentication.\r\n\r\n#7281 added AWS credential providers, so we could potentially have an `s3_auth` http filter that uses that and adds the needed headers. The filter would probably need to support `per_filter_config`, to allow restricting the functionality to a subset of routes.\r\n\r\nI think this sounds like a generally useful filter, so I am thinking of developing it for upstream instead of being another in-house filter.\r\n\r\nThoughts?\r\n\r\ncc: @mattklein123  @derekargueta ",
